        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If you're running the PHP application in strict mode and the file you wish to check for readability does not exist, an warning is given by PHP. \nIn my case this occurred if you validate a xyz@domain.net eMail address since in the folder \"Hostname\" is no file for .net domains.\n\nA trivial fix would be:\n{code}if (!file_exists($filename) || !$fh = @fopen($filename, 'r', true)) {{code}\n\ninstead of:\n{code}if (!$fh = @fopen($filename, 'r', true)) {{code}"
        },
